  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.header": "Thruster",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_1": "Thrusters burn liquid fuel to produce directional thrust",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_2": "Any '#c:fuel' tagged fluid works. A pump moves it from the tank into the thruster",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_3": "Any rotational source works. A Cogwheel linking the pump's axle is one clean option",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_4": "An Analog Lever (or any analog redstone signal) acts as the throttle",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_5": "Stronger signals burn more fuel per tick and push harder",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_6": "Drop the signal to zero and the engine shuts off. No burn, no thrust",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_7": "Shift-right-click with a Wrench to toggle Binary mode",
  "aerothrusters.ponder.thruster_overview.text_8": "In Binary mode, the thruster runs at full power whenever it receives any redstone signal"
